    <section id="postingbody">
        <div class="print-information print-qrcode-container">
            <p class="print-qrcode-label">QR Code Link to This Post</p>
            <div class="print-qrcode" data-location="http://chicago.craigslist.org/wcl/fbh/6042154513.html"></div>
        </div>
Hotel Arista is not a chain, rather, we're something a little different. We're an independent, locally owned boutique hotel and something of a maverick. We offer effortless and luxurious accommodations for business, leisure and weddings.<br>
<br>
Our guests are people who like to write their own story -- leaders, innovators, high-profile couples, chic brides, authors, actors, film crews and more. This is a crowd that likes the seduction of an effortless, evocative experience and the glamor of making a place their own.<br>
<br>
Personal taste and choice are considered paramount at Hotel Arista, and guests select from an extensive personal preference menu of amenities and services.Hotel Arista at CityGate Centre in Naperville is a four-diamond award winner and the first LEED certified hotel in Illinois.<br>
<br>
Role Summary:<br>
<br>
The Stewarding Supervisor role is to supervise the day-to-day operation of the department for a given shift. The Stewarding Supervisor is responsible for the control and distribution of operating equipment, maintenance of cleaning and sanitation standards, supervision of all utility, pot washer, dishwasher, and worker assignment tasks. This is a working supervisory position.<br>
<br>
Responsibilities:<br>
-Implement the Standard Operating Procedures for the Stewarding department with guidance from Chefs<br>
-Maintain and strictly abide by state sanitation/health regulation and hotel requirements<br>
-Meet with Executive Chef/ Banquet Chef to review assignments, anticipated business levels, changes and other information pertinent to the operation.<br>
-Develop a cleaning schedule for kitchen, pastry, garde manger, banquets, cafeteria, and coolers.<br>
-Continue to keep all special event storerooms clean and organized<br>
-Responsible for the requisition of all products utilized in the stewarding area<br>
-Stocking all storage areas when shipments are received.<br>
-Inspect the cleanliness and working condition of all tools, equipment and supplies, ensure everything complies with standards.<br>
-Quarterly inventory of china, glasses, silverware and hollowware from the outlets and main storage.<br>
-Establish and maintain accurate par levels of china, glass silver inventory.<br>
-Provide enough equipment (china, glass, silver) to the outlets and banquet for their operation.<br>
-Requisition and organization of chemical supplies<br>
-Assist and provide equipment for all banquets functions.<br>
-Assist banquet kitchen team with plate up, when necessary.<br>
-Provide supervisory guidance and assistance to all colleagues in the Stewarding Department<br>
-Work with the Executive Chef/ Banquet Chef on weekly schedule for stewarding staff<br>
-Responsible for the cleanliness of the back dock, employee entrance and first floor hallway area.<br>
-Revise standard and procedures for the department, as necessary with approval of Executive Chef/ Banquet Chef<br>
-Create a safe and secure environment for all guests and colleagues.<br>
-Assist anywhere else in the F&B department to ensure effortless guest experiences and continuity in service<br>
-Report to work in proper uniform and ensure Stewarding department is in proper uniform as well<br>
-Covers shifts as needed according to business levels and budget restriction<br>
-Other duties as assigned.<br>
<br>
Minimum Qualifications:<br>
-A minimum of 2 years' experience in a luxury market.<br>
-1- 2 years' experience in supervisory skills.<br>
-Speak fluent of English, read and write.<br>
-Must be willing to work a flexible schedule in order to accomplish all major responsibilities and tasks.<br>
-Must be able to relate to all levels of management.<br>
-Must be self-motivator and motivate others.<br>
-Must work in a safe, prudent and organized manner.<br>
-Must have the ability to handle multiple tasks at one time.<br>
-Must have superior organizational skills.<br>
-Must have mathematical skills, Computer software aptitude and some hotel operations.<br>
<br>
We are an equal opportunity employer and make employment decisions without regard to age, race, religion, national origin, gender, disability, veteran status, genetic information, sexual orientation and gender identity or any other protected class. Our locations are drug-free and pre-employment drug tests are required. Background checks are also required before employment begins. <br>
<br>
We participate in E-Verify and those who are ineligible to work in the United States will not be considered.    </section>

